******
[3] Dominican Republic update
Date: Tue 28 Dec 2010
Source: Info Sur Hoy [trans. Corr.SB, edited]
<http://infosurhoy.com/cocoon/saii/xhtml/es/newsbriefs/saii/newsbriefs/20=10/12/28/newsbrief-02>


Authorities are investigating the death of an unidentified person who
allegedly would have been the 1st fatality of the cholera outbreak
that began in mid-October 2010. According to statements by the
Minister of Health, Bautista Rojas, 105 people in the country have
contracted cholera.

According to the authorities, the person who allegedly died on 23 Dec
2010 as a result of the disease is a farmer aged 37, a resident of San
Juan de la Maguana, a city west of the country near the border with
Haiti.

"There has been an outbreak (of disease) in the provinces of San Juan
and Azua," Rojas said at a news conference.

